[SN]TITLE[SN]
David Martin: Bromley sign former Crystal Palace and Derby winger

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
National League side Bromley have signed winger David Martin following his departure from Whitehawk.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 31-year-old helped the Hawks reach the National League South play-offs last season.
Martin previously had spells with Crystal Palace, Millwall, Derby, Southend, Luton and Stevenage.
"David will be a key member of the squad for us this season. He has plenty of league experience," Ravens manager Neil Smith told the club website.
Bromley have not disclosed the length of Martin's deal.
